<li>For **Denied logging interval**, set the per-second rate limit for  packets blocked by either a container-specific [networking policy](../concepts/understand-cf-networking.html#policies) or by [Application Security Group](../opsguide/app-sec-groups.html) rules applied across the space, org, or deployment. This field defaults to <code>1</code>.</li>
<li>For **UDP logging interval**, set the per-second rate limit for UDP packets sent and received. This field defaults to <code>100</code>.</li>
<li>To enable logging for app traffic, select **Log traffic for all accepted/denied application packets**. See [Manage Logging for Container-to-Container Networking](../opsguide/logging-config-opsman.html#app-traffic-log) for more information.</li>